{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489867","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489867"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:33:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:33:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"765"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"765","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/765"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.05,0.16,0.53,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"765"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59021"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"765","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/765"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"765"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44432"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1217"},{"type":"tags","id":"3461"},{"type":"tags","id":"4208"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"715"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1758"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18123"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42141"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44475"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59021","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/59021"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA previously well 46-year-old man presents with a one day history of severe and constant right upper quadrant pain. On examination his blood pressure is 110/70 mmHg, pulse 104/min and temperature 38.4C. His abdomen is soft, apart from localised tenderness in the right upper quadrant. An abdominal ultrasound examination is performed.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following findings would be most supportive of the likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["A 3 cm stone impacted in Hartmann\u0027s pouch","Numerous small stones in the fundus of the gallbladder","Dilatation of the intrahepatic biliary tree","A thick-walled gallbladder","An echogenic focus at the neck of the gallbladder"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe patient almost certainly has acute cholecystitis. This diagnosis would be confirmed by the finding of a \u003Cstrong\u003Ethick-walled gallbladder\u003C/strong\u003E - suggesting inflammation and oedema. A thick-walled gallbladder is defined as \u0026gt;3mm. A thickness of 3 - 4 mm gives a moderate indication of inflammation and over 5mm would be very much in keeping with a diagnosis of acute cholecystitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECertainly the findings of gallstones would be supportive of this diagnosis, but thickening of the gallbladder wall would be more clear-cut evidence. A stone impacted in Hartmann\u0027s pouch or in the neck of the gallbladder might suggest gallbladder obstruction and biliary colic - but that is not the clinical diagnosis in this case. Dilatation of the biliary tree in these circumstances could be in keeping with Mirizzi\u0027s syndrome. However, this condition of a gallstone at the neck of the gallbladder causing common bile duct obstruction is relatively rare and is not always associated with an acute inflammatory process.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The ultrasonographic appearance of thickening of the gallbladder wall supports a diagnosis of acute cholecystitis."],"references":["Halpin V. Acute cholecystitis. BMJ Clin Evid. 2014. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25144428/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44432"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"765"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44432","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/44432"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-04T13:19:55+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-04T13:21:16+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"765"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59021"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\u200d\u2620\ufe0f","name":"Radiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-15T15:37:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"65","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/65"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","n